'''tuyere'''
# A [[nozzle]], [[mouthpiece]], or [[fixture]] through which the [[blast]] is delivered to the interior of a blast [[furnace]], or to the fire of a [[forge]]. [Corruptly written also {tweer}, and {twier}.]
